{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/596","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/596/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/596/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blevesearch/bleve/issues/596/events","html_url":"https://github.com/blevesearch/bleve/issues/596","id":231186621,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMzExODY2MjE=","number":596,"title":"Any way to determine which subdocuments for hit locations?","user":{"login":"caseymrm","id":124769,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNDc2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/124769?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm","html_url":"https://github.com/caseymrm","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/caseymrm/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2017-05-24T22:13:29Z","updated_at":"2017-05-25T15:48:43Z","closed_at":"2017-05-25T15:48:43Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hello, thank you for Bleve!\r\n\r\nWhen using IncludeLocations and sub-documents, I haven't been able to find a way to determine which sub-document the Hit.Location applies to (or more generally which sub-document(s) triggered the hit, which could be useful to know even when not using locations).\r\n\r\nHere's a contrived example: https://play.golang.org/p/-QKGWUQkfO\r\n\r\nWhen run, it produces:\r\n\r\n```\r\nField Emails.Subject = [horse cat monkey apple pear banana]\r\nField Id = thread1\r\nField Emails.Id = [email1 email2]\r\n    Field Emails.Subject has term cat from 6 to 9 (Pos 2?)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat I'd like to know is that \"cat\" was found in the Subject of \"email1\", not \"email2\".\r\n\r\nCurrently the only way I see to do it is to go back and look at each Subject myself, checking positions 6-9 until I find which email has a matching Subject.\r\n\r\nBased on the way Emails.Subject contains the subjects concatenated, I don't have high hopes that the data on which sub-document is accessible when constructing the Location, but since the returned positions are relative to the original strings I thought I'd double-check.\r\n\r\nThanks for any insights!","closed_by":{"login":"mschoch","id":298143,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI5ODE0Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/298143?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch","html_url":"https://github.com/mschoch","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mschoch/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users